    "intro": "Scorzonera subintegra, also known as Autumn Scorzonera, is a perennial plant in the dandelion family (Asteraceae) native to Europe and parts of Asia. The plant is valued for its potential health benefits, including the ability to lower blood sugar levels, reduce inflammation, and support digestive health due to its prebiotic properties. The bioactive constituents of Scorzonera subintegra include inulin, a type of fructan, as well as other saponins and phenolic compounds that may contribute to its medicinal properties. Scorzonera subintegra is commonly used in herbal preparations such as teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are often used to support weight management and promote overall well-being."
